  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Add the <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>smoked paprika</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> to a plate</p><p>Add a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>spice mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> to the <strong>spice mix</strong> and turn them several times until the chicken is coated in all of the spices</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until beginning to brown</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Once the chicken has browned, add the <strong>tomato stock</strong> to the pan and reduce the heat to medium</p><p>Cook, covered, turning occasionally for a further 10 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks (save some leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> with 2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Grind to a paste then add the <strong>mayo</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>coriander mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the chicken to a clean board and shred it apart, using two forks - this technique is known as ‘pulling’</p><p>Divide the <strong>pulled</strong> <strong>chicken </strong>and<strong> sauce</strong> evenly between the <strong>tortillas</strong></p><p>Roll each <strong>filled</strong> <strong>tortilla</strong> up and arrange them into an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p><p>Drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and put the dish in the oven for 15 min or until beginning to crisp – these are your<strong> chicken taquitos</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2110.-step-5-x400.jpg",
